import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['x'] = pd.to_datetime(data['x'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    plt.scatter(data['x'], data['y'])
    plt.title('What is the correlation between X and Y?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['x'] = pd.to_datetime(data['x'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    plt.hist(data['x'], bins=20, color='blue', edgecolor='black')
    plt.axvline(data['x'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['x'].median()))
    plt.legend(loc='upper right')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of X?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['y'].plot(kind='hist', bins=20, color='blue', edgecolor='black')
    plt.axvline(data['y'].median(), color='red', label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['y'].median()))
    plt.title('What is the distribution of Y?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['quadrant'] = pd.cut(data['x'], bins=2, labels=['left', 'right']) + pd.cut(data['y'], bins=2, labels=['bottom', 'top'])
    quadrant_counts = data['quadrant'].value_counts()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.bar(quadrant_counts.index, quadrant_counts.values)
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of data points across quadrants?')
    ax.set_xlabel('Quadrant')
    ax.set_ylabel('Count')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['quadrant'] = data['quadrant'].astype(str)
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.boxplot([data[data['quadrant'] == '1']['x'], data[data['quadrant'] == '2']['x'], data[data['quadrant'] == '3']['x'], data[data['quadrant'] == '4']['x']], labels=['1', '2', '3', '4'])
    ax.set_xlabel('Quadrant')
    ax.set_ylabel('X')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between X and quadrant?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
